<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-37-0606 </DOCNO><TEXT>The disaster at Chernobyl did not happen only due to human failure. Thedevelopment was supported by the Soviet mental attitude to science andtechnology, according to which projects of Soviet scientists and technologistsare regarded to be infallible. From the Russian point of view, thereis no reason to reconsider the risks of the peaceful use of nuclear energy.</TEXT></DOC>